riscv-skyline
=============

The bulk of this repository (kernel drivers, the eight assembly drawing
primitives in `kernel/mp1.S`, the allocator in `kernel/memory.c`, the
test bench, the documentation, the build and CI configuration) was
authored by Yoonkyu Lee and is distributed under the MIT License (see
LICENSE).

One file is *not* original to this repo:

  kernel/vendor/demo.o

`demo.o` is the starter scaffolding's drawing-loop driver -- it
provides `main`, scans PCI for the bochs-display, calls `vga_attach`,
seeds the scene (stars / lit windows / beacon positions), and runs the
per-frame redraw loop that calls into the eight primitives in
`mp1.S`. The original source is not distributed with the starter, so
the binary is checked in as-is. It produces the visual style the
README hero shot shows.

A clean-room replacement for `demo.o` is straightforward (~150 LOC of
C against the `skyline.h` API and `vga.c` driver) and was prototyped
during development; the vendor binary was kept because the original
scene composition reads more like a real night skyline than the
clean-room re-imagining did.
